cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is about a recommendation system for offline book retail, which involves natural language processing techniques such as LDA and word2vec. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with techniques for searching and recommending information. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as collaborative filtering, which falls under sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of natural language processing techniques also suggests sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
